B.UQ=new A.bJ('Kasilo Choka is "The Curator" of Grownhop Records and the has been a silent influencer to the hip hop community.\n\nIn the 80\'s he was know as MC Kid Krush from San Jose, California.  His protege was MC Charizma and he introduced Stones Throw Records Owner/ Producer Peanut Butter Wolf to Charizma. He\'s worked with many artists from Producer Mad Hat aka Ancient Carbon, MC Prime Artist, Kev Brown of Low Budget,MC Fatal of Austin, Jackie Chain, JPZ aka  Rec Tha BEATZ Producer of E-40, Mr. Williams, Producer JKnodik, Producer Cafe, Question of San Antonio plus DJ Screw of Houston, Texas and many others.\n\nKasilo Choka released a special album dedicated to the streets of Oakland, California where he was born.  The album "Family Business" was curated, arranged and self produced and self distributed for the memory of The Life of Oscar Grant. ',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
